<task id="011" project="file-preview-dialog-with-auth-enhancements">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement Open File and Open Record Toolbar Actions</title>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>fluent-ui, toolbar, navigation</tags>
    <estimate>2-3 hours</estimate>
    <dependencies>010</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <goal>Implement Open File and Open Record toolbar actions in FilePreviewDialog</goal>
    <context>
      The FilePreviewDialog toolbar has 4 actions. This task implements the first two: Open File
      (which opens the document for editing/viewing) and Open Record (which navigates to the
      Dataverse record). Open File uses a lazy-fetch pattern — the open links are fetched on first
      click, not on dialog open — to avoid unnecessary API calls. It cascades through desktop app,
      web app, then download as fallback. Open Record uses the standard Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo
      pattern to open the sprk_document entity record.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST lazy-fetch open links on first click (not on dialog open) to minimize API calls
      - MUST cascade: desktop app → web app → download (first available wins)
      - MUST use DocumentApiService.getDocumentOpenLinks() for fetching links
      - MUST use navigateToEntity for Open Record navigation
      - MUST show loading indicator on Open File button during fetch
      - MUST handle errors gracefully (toast or inline message)
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/services/DocumentApiService.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/services/navigation.ts</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/oauth-scopes.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read DocumentApiService.ts for getDocumentOpenLinks() signature and response shape</step>
    <step>Read navigation.ts for navigateToEntity helper and entity navigation pattern</step>
    <step>Implement Open File click handler with lazy fetch of DocumentApiService.getDocumentOpenLinks()</step>
    <step>Implement 3-tier cascade logic: try desktop URL first, fall back to web URL, then download URL</step>
    <step>Add isLoadingOpenLinks state and show Spinner on Open File button during fetch</step>
    <step>Cache open links after first fetch to avoid redundant API calls on subsequent clicks</step>
    <step>Implement Open Record click handler using navigateToEntity({ action: 'openRecord', entityName: 'sprk_document', entityId: documentId })</step>
    <step>Add error handling for both actions (catch and display user-friendly messages)</step>
    <step>Verify TypeScript compiles without errors</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <output>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx (updated)</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Open File button triggers lazy fetch of open links on first click</criterion>
    <criterion>Open links cascade: desktop → web → download</criterion>
    <criterion>Open links are cached after first fetch</criterion>
    <criterion>Loading indicator shown on Open File button during fetch</criterion>
    <criterion>Open Record navigates to sprk_document entity record</criterion>
    <criterion>Errors are handled gracefully without crashing the dialog</criterion>
    <criterion>TypeScript compiles without errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
